1
00:00:33,346 --> 00:00:38,059
AGENT KIM REACTIVATED

2
00:00:41,896 --> 00:00:44,649
-Min-ji.
-Hey, what a great house!

3
00:00:44,732 --> 00:00:46,025
It's nice and big.

4
00:00:46,109 --> 00:00:48,111
What are you talking about?
It obviously looks small.

5
00:00:49,529 --> 00:00:52,073
Min-ji, come inside. It's dangerous.

6
00:00:53,491 --> 00:00:55,994
-I'd say about ten…
-Come in!

7
00:00:56,077 --> 00:00:57,996
Well, maybe eight people could live here.

8
00:00:58,079 --> 00:00:59,205
Move some boxes already.

9
00:00:59,289 --> 00:01:00,456
EPISODE 5

10
00:01:06,713 --> 00:01:09,549
Hey, why didn't you mention
there was no elevator?

11
00:01:10,508 --> 00:01:12,385
If I'd known, I wouldn't have come.

12
00:01:13,928 --> 00:01:15,221
You can go now.

13
00:01:15,889 --> 00:01:16,723
Really?

14
00:01:17,473 --> 00:01:19,267
Since you have a hired hand here,

15
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:20,310
I'll just take off.

16
00:01:21,144 --> 00:01:22,437
Where do you think you're going?

17
00:01:22,520 --> 00:01:25,523
Stop whining.
Go downstairs and move some boxes.

18
00:01:26,649 --> 00:01:27,650
What kind of athlete

19
00:01:27,734 --> 00:01:30,194
can't put any muscle into it
and only moves the light stuff?

20
00:01:30,278 --> 00:01:32,822
If I had any muscle,
I would've become a weightlifter.

21
00:01:32,906 --> 00:01:33,740
What did you say?

22
00:01:33,823 --> 00:01:35,950
Taekwondo isn't about strength.

23
00:01:36,034 --> 00:01:37,368
Get out of my way already!

24
00:01:37,452 --> 00:01:38,578
You can't pivot, can you?

25
00:01:39,787 --> 00:01:41,831
-Jeez.
-You're all muscle and no brain.

26
00:01:41,915 --> 00:01:43,207
You need to use your head.

27
00:01:43,291 --> 00:01:45,835
Move out of the way
before I throw this at you.

28
00:01:45,919 --> 00:01:47,045
Gosh, it's cold.

29
00:01:47,962 --> 00:01:49,172
This is so good.

30
00:01:49,255 --> 00:01:50,340
Thank you, sir.

31
00:01:50,423 --> 00:01:51,966
Sure thing. Come by again.

32
00:01:52,050 --> 00:01:53,301
-Okay.
-Okay.

33
00:01:55,136 --> 00:01:56,304
Who wants to go to the playground?

34
00:01:56,387 --> 00:01:57,430
-Me!
-Me too!

35
00:01:57,513 --> 00:01:59,474
But I have to go to my academy class.

36
00:02:01,517 --> 00:02:02,769
Did you just move here?

37
00:02:05,521 --> 00:02:06,356
Yeah.

38
00:02:06,439 --> 00:02:08,191
Want to come to the playground with us?

39
00:02:11,694 --> 00:02:12,737
You lift this one.

40
00:02:13,947 --> 00:02:14,822
Move this fridge.

41
00:02:18,159 --> 00:02:19,035
Min-ji.

42
00:02:21,120 --> 00:02:22,121
What is it?

43
00:02:22,205 --> 00:02:23,122
Min-ji!

44
00:02:25,291 --> 00:02:26,668
-What's wrong?
-Where is she?

45
00:02:29,254 --> 00:02:30,088
Min-ji!

46
00:02:30,171 --> 00:02:31,339
Min-ji's gone.

47
00:02:32,173 --> 00:02:33,925
-Min-ji!
-Where did she go?

48
00:02:38,429 --> 00:02:39,305
Min-ji!

49
00:02:39,389 --> 00:02:41,557
-Min-ji!
-Kim Min-ji!

50
00:02:42,058 --> 00:02:43,351
Min-ji!

51
00:02:43,935 --> 00:02:44,894
Min-ji!

52
00:02:46,854 --> 00:02:47,981
Min-ji!

53
00:02:48,064 --> 00:02:49,107
Min-ji!

54
00:02:49,190 --> 00:02:50,316
-I'll go this way.
-Okay.

55
00:02:51,109 --> 00:02:52,110
Min-ji!

56
00:02:53,277 --> 00:02:54,112
Min-ji!

57
00:02:54,195 --> 00:02:56,239
-Hide your toes, hide your nose
-Hey.

58
00:02:56,322 --> 00:02:58,116
-Here I come
-Where are you going to hide?

59
00:02:58,199 --> 00:03:00,660
-You go this way, and I'll go that way.
-Hide your toes, hide your nose

60
00:03:00,743 --> 00:03:02,787
Here I come

61
00:03:02,870 --> 00:03:04,789
-Good luck.
-Hide your toes, hide your nose

62
00:03:04,872 --> 00:03:07,000
Here I come

63
00:03:07,083 --> 00:03:10,962
Hide your toes, hide your nose
Here I come

64
00:03:11,045 --> 00:03:15,383
Hide your toes, hide your nose
Here I come

65
00:03:15,466 --> 00:03:17,427
Hide your toes, hide your nose

66
00:03:17,510 --> 00:03:19,512
JEILWON SENIOR WELFARE CENTER

67
00:03:33,234 --> 00:03:35,194
-Min-ji!
-Min-ji!

68
00:03:42,618 --> 00:03:43,745
Let's keep looking.

69
00:03:43,828 --> 00:03:44,746
Come on.

70
00:04:11,397 --> 00:04:12,315
Min-ji!

71
00:04:13,775 --> 00:04:14,776
Min-ji!

72
00:04:15,485 --> 00:04:16,861
I'm sorry,

73
00:04:16,944 --> 00:04:18,654
but have you seen this child?

74
00:04:19,405 --> 00:04:21,199
No, we haven't seen her.

75
00:04:21,282 --> 00:04:22,533
Thank you.

76
00:04:24,494 --> 00:04:25,411
Hey, Kim!

77
00:04:25,495 --> 00:04:26,871
-Yeah?
-Any sign?

78
00:04:27,580 --> 00:04:28,414
No.

79
00:04:30,124 --> 00:04:31,292
Let's head back home.

80
00:04:31,376 --> 00:04:32,335
Maybe she's back.

81
00:04:32,919 --> 00:04:34,420
-All right.
-Come on.

82
00:04:35,213 --> 00:04:36,047
Min-ji!

83
00:04:42,762 --> 00:04:44,097
Have they all left?

84
00:04:44,806 --> 00:04:46,349
Is anyone here?

85
00:04:46,432 --> 00:04:47,642
I'm locking up now.

86
00:04:54,649 --> 00:04:57,402
CURRENTLY AWAY

87
00:05:44,866 --> 00:05:45,992
Excuse me!

88
00:05:47,952 --> 00:05:49,078
Over here!

89
00:05:53,541 --> 00:05:54,917
Over here!

90
00:05:59,839 --> 00:06:01,632
-Is she home?
-No.

91
00:06:01,716 --> 00:06:02,842
Where did she go?

92
00:06:02,925 --> 00:06:04,719
I went to the apartment complex,
but she's not there.

93
00:06:05,303 --> 00:06:06,512
My goodness.

94
00:06:06,596 --> 00:06:08,389
She was right here.

95
00:06:08,472 --> 00:06:11,267
Why didn't you keep an eye on her?

96
00:06:12,310 --> 00:06:14,228
Goodness gracious.

97
00:06:15,021 --> 00:06:16,522
-Did you check the park?
-Jeez.

98
00:06:17,148 --> 00:06:19,150
-Min-ji!
-She was literally right here.

99
00:06:22,236 --> 00:06:23,154
Kim Min-ji!

100
00:06:26,991 --> 00:06:28,326
She was right here.

101
00:06:28,409 --> 00:06:29,702
Daddy!

102
00:06:34,457 --> 00:06:35,541
Min-ji!

103
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:36,542
-Hey!
-Min-ji!

104
00:06:37,126 --> 00:06:38,336
Daddy!

105
00:06:38,419 --> 00:06:39,712
-Min-ji!
-Hey!

106
00:06:46,677 --> 00:06:49,597
Where did you go?
I looked everywhere for you.

107
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:50,514
Are you okay?

108
00:06:51,807 --> 00:06:55,561
I was playing hide-and-seek
at the playground.

109
00:06:56,312 --> 00:06:59,065
I couldn't open the door to get out,

110
00:06:59,607 --> 00:07:01,734
but I didn't cry.

111
00:07:01,817 --> 00:07:04,195
Goodness, Min-ji. You're so brave.

112
00:07:06,364 --> 00:07:07,198
Thank you.

113
00:07:07,281 --> 00:07:08,824
It must've been hard to find this place.

114
00:07:08,908 --> 00:07:11,285
Min-ji told me where to go,
so it was easy.

115
00:07:11,369 --> 00:07:12,286
She's very smart.

116
00:07:13,704 --> 00:07:15,831
There's the fish-shaped bun stand,

117
00:07:15,915 --> 00:07:17,166
the post office box,

118
00:07:18,584 --> 00:07:20,086
and the red house.

119
00:07:21,337 --> 00:07:22,421
Min-ji needs to hit the books.

120
00:07:23,005 --> 00:07:23,965
-She'll be successful.
-That's right.

121
00:07:24,048 --> 00:07:28,469
Have her study to become a doctor or judge
so she can help us out later.

122
00:07:29,053 --> 00:07:30,805
Jeez, that's all you can think of?

123
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:32,765
From now on,

124
00:07:33,432 --> 00:07:35,851
you can't go off on your own, okay?

125
00:07:40,022 --> 00:07:40,856
It's okay.

126
00:07:40,940 --> 00:07:43,067
I'm sorry, Daddy.

127
00:07:46,112 --> 00:07:47,113
Are you okay?

128
00:07:47,196 --> 00:07:48,864
Yeah, I'm okay.

129
00:07:49,907 --> 00:07:51,325
-I'm sorry.
-Thank you.

130
00:07:57,331 --> 00:07:58,791
It's okay.

131
00:08:03,963 --> 00:08:05,840
AGENT KIM REACTIVATED

132
00:08:27,570 --> 00:08:28,529
Hey!

133
00:08:31,657 --> 00:08:32,533
Hey!

134
00:08:34,452 --> 00:08:36,871
Open the door!

135
00:08:37,872 --> 00:08:39,957
Wait a minute. What's going on?

136
00:08:41,292 --> 00:08:42,126
She's alive?

137
00:08:44,170 --> 00:08:45,296
What the hell?

138
00:08:45,379 --> 00:08:46,339
Hey!

139
00:08:47,381 --> 00:08:49,216
Hey, kid!

140
00:08:52,762 --> 00:08:54,013
Stay in there for a second.

141
00:08:54,096 --> 00:08:54,930
Hold on.

142
00:08:57,266 --> 00:08:58,392
What the heck?

143
00:09:00,978 --> 00:09:02,188
Who the hell are you?

144
00:09:04,315 --> 00:09:06,400
I'm sorry. Please.

145
00:09:06,484 --> 00:09:07,401
I'm sorry.

146
00:09:07,485 --> 00:09:09,195
Why isn't he answering? Damn it!

147
00:09:13,908 --> 00:09:14,867
Hello?

148
00:09:15,368 --> 00:09:16,911
Boss, this is Seok-jung.

149
00:09:16,994 --> 00:09:19,121
We're almost there. Where do you want us?

150
00:09:19,205 --> 00:09:21,123
Hey, did you bring the guys?

151
00:09:21,207 --> 00:09:22,249
Yes, I brought all of them.

152
00:09:22,833 --> 00:09:24,669
Go to the office.

153
00:09:24,752 --> 00:09:27,129
Sang-man and Gang-min aren't answering.

154
00:09:27,213 --> 00:09:28,089
Got it, boss.

155
00:10:01,122 --> 00:10:02,623
Who the hell are you?

156
00:10:03,666 --> 00:10:06,836
Why are you going this far over some girl?

157
00:10:07,753 --> 00:10:09,171
Did Ju Gang-chan send you?

158
00:10:10,423 --> 00:10:11,257
Ju Gang-chan?

159
00:10:11,841 --> 00:10:12,883
No?

160
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:14,385
Then who are you?

161
00:10:15,177 --> 00:10:16,637
Are you a cop?

162
00:10:20,182 --> 00:10:21,350
Tell me.

163
00:10:22,268 --> 00:10:23,102
Where's Min-ji?

164
00:10:25,438 --> 00:10:27,356
The cold storage warehouse.

165
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:29,024
She's frozen in there.

166
00:10:29,859 --> 00:10:30,693
Go take a look.

167
00:10:31,819 --> 00:10:33,654
I said go take a look!

168
00:10:33,738 --> 00:10:34,989
Cold storage warehouse?

169
00:10:38,117 --> 00:10:39,201
My Min-ji…

170
00:10:40,953 --> 00:10:45,124
Look, all we did was move her
after Ju Gang-chan's daughter called us.

171
00:10:45,207 --> 00:10:47,418
She was dead from the start!

172
00:10:58,763 --> 00:10:59,764
If…

173
00:11:01,891 --> 00:11:04,185
Min-ji is really dead…

174
00:11:06,353 --> 00:11:07,188
I'm going to…

175
00:11:09,148 --> 00:11:10,691
kill all of you.

176
00:11:37,593 --> 00:11:40,137
That crazy bastard. No, I refuse to die.

177
00:11:55,945 --> 00:11:58,405
Nothing beat the MG42 during World War II.

178
00:11:58,489 --> 00:11:59,323
"Hitler's Buzzsaw."

179
00:11:59,406 --> 00:12:00,574
You've seen Saving Private Ryan, right?

180
00:12:00,658 --> 00:12:03,202
The Germans used it
to spray everyone in Normandy.

181
00:12:03,285 --> 00:12:05,829
Man, 1,200 rounds per minute
back then is insane, isn't it?

182
00:12:05,913 --> 00:12:08,040
At 1,200 rounds per minute,
how many rounds is that in a second?

183
00:12:08,791 --> 00:12:10,543
How many rounds is that? Huh?

184
00:12:10,626 --> 00:12:11,585
Did you learn arithmetic?

185
00:12:11,669 --> 00:12:13,671
That's 20 rounds per second.

186
00:12:15,339 --> 00:12:16,257
That's no joke.

187
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:19,927
It's such a shame
we can only see it in museums now.

188
00:12:20,010 --> 00:12:21,470
-Isn't it a shame?
-Not really.

189
00:12:21,554 --> 00:12:22,721
Are you still doing the math?

190
00:12:22,805 --> 00:12:26,976
Man, what a mess.

191
00:12:27,977 --> 00:12:29,019
Why are you acting sentimental?

192
00:12:30,354 --> 00:12:31,397
I have to say,

193
00:12:32,398 --> 00:12:35,192
life was easier
when I was just ironing clothes.

194
00:12:35,276 --> 00:12:38,862
It would've been easier for Agent Kim
to live an ordinary life too, right?

195
00:12:38,946 --> 00:12:42,283
I mean, he was the easiest guy
to push around.

196
00:12:42,366 --> 00:12:46,704
Sometimes, I wasn't even sure
if he was really 66.

197
00:12:46,787 --> 00:12:47,830
Well, I'm still not sure.

198
00:12:47,913 --> 00:12:50,165
If I were him,

199
00:12:50,249 --> 00:12:54,253
our deputy branch manager would've been
found dead somewhere a long time ago.

200
00:12:56,964 --> 00:12:59,842
The M249 is the most similar to it,
if anything.

201
00:12:59,925 --> 00:13:03,178
Of course, it uses 5.56 mm NATO rounds,
and it's more compact,

202
00:13:03,262 --> 00:13:04,597
so some say it lacks firepower.

203
00:13:04,680 --> 00:13:07,850
But at 1,150 rounds per minute,
it's still pretty sweet.

204
00:13:07,933 --> 00:13:10,102
Tell you the truth, I own a few myself.

205
00:13:10,185 --> 00:13:11,812
Want to see them sometime?
Aren't you curious?

206
00:13:12,521 --> 00:13:15,107
Hey, don't underestimate it
just because it's compact.

207
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:17,735
It's modular, so you can run
whatever attachments you need,

208
00:13:17,818 --> 00:13:20,279
which is why the M249 is great.

209
00:13:20,362 --> 00:13:21,864
We've located the director.

210
00:13:21,947 --> 00:13:23,741
All units move out,
except for the HQ escort vehicle.

211
00:13:36,795 --> 00:13:37,880
Everyone's done for the day, huh?

212
00:13:39,465 --> 00:13:41,008
Well, in that case,

213
00:13:41,091 --> 00:13:43,260
this is the end of today's lesson.

214
00:13:55,022 --> 00:13:56,023
You guys should go home too.

215
00:14:13,707 --> 00:14:14,750
Get it together.

216
00:15:07,636 --> 00:15:09,346
That bastard's back.

217
00:15:10,597 --> 00:15:11,557
What now?

218
00:15:12,933 --> 00:15:15,310
Holy crap, he's coming! What do I do?

219
00:15:23,027 --> 00:15:24,236
He's coming again!

220
00:15:42,254 --> 00:15:43,130
Oh no.

221
00:16:01,982 --> 00:16:03,484
All right!

222
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:04,902
I made it!

223
00:16:04,985 --> 00:16:06,862
Good job.

224
00:16:14,203 --> 00:16:16,163
Are you there? What happened?

225
00:16:16,246 --> 00:16:19,166
I think something went down, boss.

226
00:16:20,209 --> 00:16:21,043
What?

227
00:16:22,836 --> 00:16:24,463
I think Sang-man is dead,

228
00:16:25,964 --> 00:16:27,299
and I don't see Gang-min at all.

229
00:16:28,425 --> 00:16:30,010
Don't tell me Ju Gang-chan…

230
00:16:31,845 --> 00:16:34,056
No, it's too early for him to be there.

231
00:16:35,641 --> 00:16:36,767
Hey.

232
00:16:36,850 --> 00:16:41,605
Find Gang-min and bring everyone
to the cold storage warehouse.

233
00:16:42,481 --> 00:16:43,440
Yes, boss.

234
00:17:20,727 --> 00:17:21,937
What the hell was that?

235
00:17:22,020 --> 00:17:23,522
-Hey, follow me.
-Yes, sir.

236
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:29,862
What the hell did I do so wrong?

237
00:17:42,541 --> 00:17:43,959
I'm sorry.

238
00:17:44,710 --> 00:17:46,253
I'm sorry.

239
00:17:47,588 --> 00:17:49,256
What?

240
00:17:50,465 --> 00:17:52,509
What?

241
00:17:53,010 --> 00:17:57,681
I swear I just did as I was told.

242
00:17:57,764 --> 00:17:59,308
Take me to the cold storage warehouse.

243
00:18:00,726 --> 00:18:02,227
You can die after that.

244
00:18:03,353 --> 00:18:05,647
Wait, wait…

245
00:18:26,543 --> 00:18:28,462
What kind of SMD director

246
00:18:28,545 --> 00:18:29,838
can't even swim?!

247
00:18:40,724 --> 00:18:41,934
Jeez, I'm crashing.

248
00:18:46,146 --> 00:18:47,898
What took you so long, trooper?

249
00:18:47,981 --> 00:18:49,274
You should've kept up with cardio.

250
00:18:51,568 --> 00:18:52,819
What are you doing here?

251
00:18:53,528 --> 00:18:57,449
I came to throw you a stick
in case you were struggling in the water.

252
00:18:57,532 --> 00:18:59,618
Or at least a rock.

253
00:18:59,701 --> 00:19:00,869
You little…

254
00:19:02,663 --> 00:19:04,665
How did you know I'd be here?

255
00:19:05,999 --> 00:19:08,252
Your route was obvious

256
00:19:08,335 --> 00:19:10,712
once I assessed the wind,
current, and terrain.

257
00:19:10,796 --> 00:19:13,507
I knew you'd come to the cliff area
to elude the SMD agents.

258
00:19:13,590 --> 00:19:15,592
If you'd gone down any farther,
the rapids would've swept you away.

259
00:19:15,676 --> 00:19:17,010
And across the water are thorn bushes.

260
00:19:17,094 --> 00:19:18,553
-Okay, I get it. I don't care!
-The only place

261
00:19:18,637 --> 00:19:20,681
you could've come ashore
with that dead weight

262
00:19:20,764 --> 00:19:22,057
was here.

263
00:19:22,140 --> 00:19:25,811
Of course, you have to be at my level
to figure out the exact location.

264
00:19:28,855 --> 00:19:30,857
Oh, it's working.

265
00:19:31,441 --> 00:19:32,859
What happened to the SMD agents?

266
00:19:32,943 --> 00:19:34,152
Don't worry.

267
00:19:34,236 --> 00:19:35,654
I sent them home safely.

268
00:19:35,737 --> 00:19:39,283
You probably went on about that
1,150 RPM fire-rate gun again.

269
00:19:39,366 --> 00:19:40,325
How'd you know?

270
00:19:42,286 --> 00:19:43,120
Here.

271
00:19:43,912 --> 00:19:45,038
Drink this.

272
00:19:46,456 --> 00:19:47,916
What's this?

273
00:19:48,000 --> 00:19:50,460
The way I see it,
you won't make it at this rate.

274
00:19:50,544 --> 00:19:52,921
You need to drink something like this
to stay healthy and keep up.

275
00:19:57,009 --> 00:19:58,385
You said Myeongpo Port, right?

276
00:19:58,468 --> 00:20:00,137
All right, move out!

277
00:20:00,220 --> 00:20:01,054
Hold on.

278
00:20:03,473 --> 00:20:05,600
These guys will keep coming after us.

279
00:20:06,184 --> 00:20:07,352
Let's split up.

280
00:20:09,187 --> 00:20:10,272
Don't you think

281
00:20:11,606 --> 00:20:12,858
we'll need weapons too?

282
00:20:14,609 --> 00:20:15,444
Weapons?

283
00:20:28,081 --> 00:20:30,334
Please don't kill me.

284
00:20:32,336 --> 00:20:33,879
-Sir!
-Huh?

285
00:20:35,088 --> 00:20:37,507
Hey! Why did you get here so late?

286
00:20:38,300 --> 00:20:40,177
You're dead meat.

287
00:20:41,762 --> 00:20:43,305
Hey, get this guy!

288
00:20:53,732 --> 00:20:54,816
I don't have time for this.

289
00:20:55,567 --> 00:20:56,401
Bring it.

290
00:20:57,611 --> 00:20:58,695
Kill him!

291
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,416
Hey, kid.

292
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:14,878
You'll freeze to death
if you stay in there.

293
00:21:14,961 --> 00:21:18,048
How much longer do you think
you can hold out?

294
00:21:22,719 --> 00:21:24,596
You haven't frozen to death already,
have you?

295
00:21:25,180 --> 00:21:27,265
Hey, you can't die.

296
00:21:27,349 --> 00:21:28,350
Get it together.

297
00:21:28,433 --> 00:21:29,643
What's your name?

298
00:21:30,644 --> 00:21:31,561
Dad…

299
00:21:34,398 --> 00:21:37,651
Hey, kid. How about if we make a deal?

300
00:21:37,734 --> 00:21:39,528
I'll let you go.

301
00:21:40,028 --> 00:21:41,196
Think about it.

302
00:21:41,279 --> 00:21:43,698
You and I have nothing against each other.

303
00:21:43,782 --> 00:21:45,283
We don't know each other.

304
00:21:45,367 --> 00:21:48,120
All I did was follow orders

305
00:21:48,203 --> 00:21:51,248
and bring you here
because I thought you were dead.

306
00:21:51,331 --> 00:21:52,207
Right?

307
00:21:52,290 --> 00:21:53,375
Are you listening?

308
00:21:55,877 --> 00:21:59,506
If you promise
not to tell anyone what happened,

309
00:21:59,589 --> 00:22:01,341
I'll let you go, okay?

310
00:22:01,425 --> 00:22:03,552
So just trust me--

311
00:22:03,635 --> 00:22:04,511
You're lying.

312
00:22:05,137 --> 00:22:07,055
You killed the security guard.

313
00:22:07,639 --> 00:22:09,433
You'll kill me the second I step out.

314
00:22:10,767 --> 00:22:11,977
You think I'm stupid?

315
00:22:13,562 --> 00:22:16,690
Well, I suppose
you're not a snot-nosed little kid.

316
00:22:16,773 --> 00:22:18,066
Still, I hoped you'd agree.

317
00:22:19,151 --> 00:22:21,653
Fine, go ahead and freeze to death.
I guess I'll just wait.

318
00:22:23,405 --> 00:22:26,658
Damn, why aren't these bastards here yet?

319
00:22:50,223 --> 00:22:51,349
Shall we go?

320
00:23:19,461 --> 00:23:20,378
Where is it?

321
00:23:23,173 --> 00:23:25,592
Over there. It's right over there.

322
00:24:39,207 --> 00:24:40,667
Did you find your daughter?

323
00:24:41,251 --> 00:24:42,127
What a shame.

324
00:24:45,046 --> 00:24:47,048
You'll probably never see her again.

325
00:25:36,890 --> 00:25:38,183
You fucking son of a bitch.

326
00:26:21,935 --> 00:26:23,311
Go back to where you came from.

327
00:26:26,231 --> 00:26:27,941
You've gone soft.

328
00:26:29,651 --> 00:26:31,027
Cut the crap.

329
00:26:33,488 --> 00:26:34,989
Do exactly what you did…

330
00:26:36,658 --> 00:26:37,867
when you killed my brother.

331
00:26:40,120 --> 00:26:40,954
Your brother?

332
00:26:59,055 --> 00:27:00,098
How much longer?

333
00:27:01,808 --> 00:27:03,309
We're 20 minutes away, sir.

334
00:27:05,103 --> 00:27:07,605
-Tell Nam to head over there first.
-Yes, sir.

335
00:27:08,523 --> 00:27:11,192
All units proceed to the destination,
except for the lead vehicle.

336
00:27:11,276 --> 00:27:12,735
We'll secure the area and stand by.

337
00:27:32,589 --> 00:27:34,382
Seriously, man!

338
00:27:35,633 --> 00:27:38,011
I think my ears are bleeding!

339
00:27:39,596 --> 00:27:41,598
-I can taste blood!
-Turn it off!

340
00:27:41,681 --> 00:27:42,724
Just enjoy it!

341
00:27:46,394 --> 00:27:47,604
Hey!

342
00:27:47,687 --> 00:27:49,564
Try to hold out… Are you listening?

343
00:27:49,647 --> 00:27:52,400
Hey, you guys try to hold out
until I get back!

344
00:27:52,484 --> 00:27:55,028
-Don't get scared and cry! Got it?
-Just go already.

345
00:27:55,111 --> 00:27:57,655
Rock spirit!

346
00:27:59,991 --> 00:28:01,326
What's that lunatic even saying?

347
00:28:40,240 --> 00:28:41,115
Your brother?

348
00:28:42,700 --> 00:28:43,993
What do you mean?

349
00:28:44,744 --> 00:28:45,995
You killed him.

350
00:28:50,250 --> 00:28:52,293
I'm talking about Number 66.

351
00:28:57,966 --> 00:28:58,967
Are you…

352
00:29:10,603 --> 00:29:11,437
Are you…

353
00:29:13,314 --> 00:29:14,482
Gang Seong?

354
00:29:16,276 --> 00:29:18,361
Yeong Gwang!

355
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:20,780
-Gang Seong!
-Yeong Gwang!

356
00:29:20,864 --> 00:29:24,826
-Go back! Right now!
-Yeong Gwang!

357
00:29:25,410 --> 00:29:27,078
Don't leave me behind!

358
00:29:27,161 --> 00:29:27,996
-Yeong Gwang!
-Wait for me!

359
00:29:28,079 --> 00:29:30,290
I promise to succeed
and come back for you!

360
00:29:30,915 --> 00:29:33,251
-Stay alive! You have to survive, okay?
-Yeong Gwang!

361
00:29:33,334 --> 00:29:35,420
-Yeong Gwang!
-Wait for me, Gang Seong!

362
00:29:49,767 --> 00:29:50,643
I'm not the one…

363
00:29:52,520 --> 00:29:53,813
who killed your brother.

364
00:30:05,491 --> 00:30:08,328
CRUSH THE PROVOCATIVE SCHEMES
OF THE SOUTH KOREAN PUPPETS!

365
00:30:54,123 --> 00:30:54,958
Enough.

366
00:31:30,368 --> 00:31:31,202
Take it.

367
00:31:33,329 --> 00:31:34,872
I'm giving it to you out of pity.

368
00:31:35,456 --> 00:31:36,541
You keep losing to me,

369
00:31:36,624 --> 00:31:39,168
so I was wondering
if it's because you don't eat enough.

370
00:31:43,715 --> 00:31:44,549
Thanks.

371
00:31:45,383 --> 00:31:46,259
I appreciate it.

372
00:31:47,677 --> 00:31:48,594
You bastard.

373
00:31:49,387 --> 00:31:50,513
Don't you have any pride?

374
00:31:52,765 --> 00:31:54,976
There's no such thing as pride
between friends.

375
00:31:58,896 --> 00:31:59,981
BETTER DEATH THAN ENEMY CAPTURE

376
00:32:00,064 --> 00:32:01,190
Tomorrow's finally the day.

377
00:32:02,066 --> 00:32:04,027
I'm going to make it back alive.

378
00:32:05,987 --> 00:32:08,823
They said if we complete this operation,

379
00:32:09,615 --> 00:32:11,701
they'll give us a house
and find our family.

380
00:32:11,784 --> 00:32:13,036
Family, my foot.

381
00:32:13,870 --> 00:32:16,164
I can't even remember my own name.

382
00:32:18,374 --> 00:32:19,417
Kim.

383
00:32:20,126 --> 00:32:21,252
Your last name is Kim.

384
00:32:22,712 --> 00:32:23,588
What did you say?

385
00:32:24,172 --> 00:32:25,882
Do you remember when we first came here?

386
00:32:28,634 --> 00:32:30,344
After getting beaten up for months,

387
00:32:31,721 --> 00:32:33,431
I forgot my own name.

388
00:32:34,849 --> 00:32:36,142
But for some reason,

389
00:32:36,976 --> 00:32:39,854
I never forgot that your last name is Kim.

390
00:32:42,356 --> 00:32:43,483
Isn't that funny?

391
00:32:45,026 --> 00:32:47,445
I was so scared that I forgot my own name,

392
00:32:47,528 --> 00:32:50,531
but I still remember your last name.

393
00:32:55,745 --> 00:32:56,788
Kim…

394
00:33:11,761 --> 00:33:13,304
Don't forget me.

395
00:33:15,973 --> 00:33:17,809
You're my only friend.

396
00:33:20,311 --> 00:33:21,687
If you forget me too…

397
00:33:23,606 --> 00:33:25,942
there'll be no one left to remember me.

398
00:33:31,864 --> 00:33:33,658
How can I forget my nemesis?

399
00:33:35,451 --> 00:33:38,579
I'm 73, the Republic's pride and joy.

400
00:33:39,413 --> 00:33:40,248
And you…

401
00:33:41,249 --> 00:33:43,084
You're 66, a pile of dog crap.

402
00:34:07,108 --> 00:34:08,276
Hey, 66!

403
00:34:08,985 --> 00:34:10,069
Let's get out of here!

404
00:34:19,620 --> 00:34:20,621
Hey, 66.

405
00:34:28,713 --> 00:34:30,173
Get it together.

406
00:34:30,965 --> 00:34:31,799
Let's get out of here.

407
00:34:32,550 --> 00:34:33,384
Forget it.

408
00:34:34,844 --> 00:34:36,095
Unless you can attach…

409
00:34:38,139 --> 00:34:39,015
my leg.

410
00:34:48,107 --> 00:34:49,025
Let's get out.

411
00:34:50,401 --> 00:34:51,277
This is it…

412
00:34:52,778 --> 00:34:54,280
for me.

413
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:57,825
You have to live.

414
00:35:26,062 --> 00:35:28,064
I'd rather pull the trigger than survive…

415
00:35:30,024 --> 00:35:30,983
and be taken as a prisoner.

416
00:35:32,902 --> 00:35:34,487
I won't let you die alone.

417
00:35:35,488 --> 00:35:36,489
We'll die together.

418
00:35:58,678 --> 00:35:59,845
Don't die.

419
00:36:01,138 --> 00:36:02,765
Think about why…

420
00:36:04,475 --> 00:36:06,018
we endured that hell.

421
00:36:10,106 --> 00:36:12,108
It was to survive.

422
00:36:15,528 --> 00:36:17,905
I need you to do one last thing for me.

423
00:36:26,038 --> 00:36:27,540
No matter what happens…

424
00:36:29,625 --> 00:36:30,459
promise me…

425
00:36:38,634 --> 00:36:40,094
you'll survive.

426
00:37:14,545 --> 00:37:16,505
Drop your gun! Hands on your head.

427
00:38:06,222 --> 00:38:07,306
Dad!

428
00:38:09,475 --> 00:38:11,102
Don't you have any pride at all?

429
00:38:12,478 --> 00:38:14,897
Why did you have to grovel and kneel?

430
00:38:14,980 --> 00:38:17,108
Is it because Hye-ri's dad
is a powerful man?

431
00:38:17,191 --> 00:38:18,734
I'm so ashamed.

432
00:38:18,818 --> 00:38:21,779
I feel so angry, frustrated, and pathetic.

433
00:38:22,822 --> 00:38:24,615
Why did you even have me?

434
00:38:25,449 --> 00:38:26,283
Min-ji.

435
00:38:36,669 --> 00:38:37,753
DAD

436
00:38:37,837 --> 00:38:39,505
I'm sorry for making you feel ashamed.

437
00:38:40,381 --> 00:38:42,049
But a parent's pride doesn't matter

438
00:38:42,800 --> 00:38:44,718
when it comes to their child.

439
00:38:45,719 --> 00:38:46,554
Min-ji,

440
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:48,264
you're my pride.

441
00:38:52,268 --> 00:38:53,686
I won't die, Dad.

442
00:38:54,812 --> 00:38:57,022
I'm going to survive and make it home.

443
00:39:30,848 --> 00:39:31,682
What now?

444
00:39:34,435 --> 00:39:37,396
Seriously? Now it's pouring rain too?

445
00:39:38,606 --> 00:39:40,357
You've got to be kidding me.

446
00:39:40,441 --> 00:39:43,027
It's just one thing after another, huh?

447
00:39:47,406 --> 00:39:48,324
Jeez.

448
00:39:54,288 --> 00:39:55,748
Boss!

449
00:39:57,500 --> 00:39:58,334
Gang-min!

450
00:40:00,044 --> 00:40:01,962
Hey, Gang-min.

451
00:40:02,046 --> 00:40:03,547
What's wrong with you? What happened?

452
00:40:04,507 --> 00:40:05,966
A guy

453
00:40:07,259 --> 00:40:10,387
claiming to be that girl's dad came and…

454
00:40:12,431 --> 00:40:14,350
What? Her dad?

455
00:40:14,433 --> 00:40:18,062
What are you talking about?
Why would her dad show up here?

456
00:40:19,813 --> 00:40:21,023
Hey, Gang-min.

457
00:40:23,150 --> 00:40:24,109
Is he dead?

458
00:40:25,069 --> 00:40:26,612
Hey, Gang-min!

459
00:40:35,371 --> 00:40:36,372
That's more like it.

460
00:40:37,081 --> 00:40:39,875
This is how it should be.

461
00:40:40,376 --> 00:40:42,211
You held out pretty long,

462
00:40:43,212 --> 00:40:44,129
didn't you?

463
00:41:06,110 --> 00:41:07,236
Hey, kid.

464
00:41:10,781 --> 00:41:12,741
Why are you hiding?

465
00:41:15,786 --> 00:41:18,163
Come on out. It's time to go home.

466
00:41:21,834 --> 00:41:23,252
Oh, I see.

467
00:41:24,795 --> 00:41:26,714
Are you letting me know where you are?

468
00:41:29,300 --> 00:41:34,263
Should I fall for your little plan or not?

469
00:41:35,806 --> 00:41:36,724
Let's say

470
00:41:37,558 --> 00:41:40,060
I head over there…

471
00:41:41,103 --> 00:41:42,396
Then you'll try to run!

472
00:41:45,190 --> 00:41:47,276
Or you'll come up from behind!

473
00:41:51,697 --> 00:41:52,531
Hey.

474
00:41:53,282 --> 00:41:56,577
Stop playing games and come out.

475
00:41:59,788 --> 00:42:01,707
Does it look like I'm messing around?

476
00:42:02,666 --> 00:42:05,753
If you come out now, I'll let you go.

477
00:42:05,836 --> 00:42:08,130
I'm done going easy on you!

478
00:42:16,972 --> 00:42:18,057
Bullshit.

479
00:42:30,527 --> 00:42:31,528
Hey, you're alive.

480
00:42:32,112 --> 00:42:33,614
Where are you going? Come here.

481
00:42:33,697 --> 00:42:34,907
Come here!

482
00:43:27,584 --> 00:43:29,461
You almost had me fooled.

483
00:43:32,047 --> 00:43:33,465
Don't bullshit me!

484
00:43:36,218 --> 00:43:37,386
Whatever you say,

485
00:43:38,762 --> 00:43:40,973
you're still nothing
but a traitor to the regime.

486
00:43:42,182 --> 00:43:44,268
You think I'll believe anything you say?

487
00:43:53,569 --> 00:43:54,903
You can believe me or not.

488
00:43:56,613 --> 00:43:58,198
That's your choice.

489
00:43:59,116 --> 00:44:00,200
But all of us…

490
00:44:01,285 --> 00:44:02,411
were discarded.

491
00:44:03,370 --> 00:44:04,496
Have you thought about it?

492
00:44:05,122 --> 00:44:06,832
I still don't understand.

493
00:44:06,915 --> 00:44:09,418
Why do you people need me?

494
00:44:09,501 --> 00:44:11,336
To be honest,

495
00:44:11,420 --> 00:44:14,965
I think it's a waste
to throw away talent like yours.

496
00:44:15,048 --> 00:44:19,219
I haven't seen anyone else
who can go toe-to-toe with Park Jin-cheol.

497
00:44:19,845 --> 00:44:23,682
In fact, you're probably the only one
from the North who can.

498
00:44:23,766 --> 00:44:25,434
This is your last chance.

499
00:44:25,517 --> 00:44:29,104
If you continue to hold out,
we'll have no choice but to end you.

500
00:44:30,397 --> 00:44:32,316
The North may have discarded you,

501
00:44:32,399 --> 00:44:34,526
but you still need to find a way
to make a life here.

502
00:44:34,610 --> 00:44:35,444
Don't you agree?

503
00:44:35,527 --> 00:44:36,487
"Discarded"?

504
00:44:38,071 --> 00:44:39,656
What do you mean by that?

505
00:44:39,740 --> 00:44:41,158
Didn't you know?

506
00:44:41,241 --> 00:44:42,910
You were all used as bait.

507
00:44:43,619 --> 00:44:45,662
It was your bureau's second-in-command

508
00:44:45,746 --> 00:44:48,665
who leaked the intel
that you were infiltrating that day.

509
00:44:48,749 --> 00:44:51,710
He used you guys
to get rid of the director general

510
00:44:51,794 --> 00:44:54,129
and to take his position.

511
00:44:56,548 --> 00:44:58,175
"Second-in-command"?

512
00:44:58,258 --> 00:44:59,301
DIRECTOR GENERAL RO TAE SIK

513
00:45:01,303 --> 00:45:02,471
DIRECTOR GENERAL RI EUNG RYEONG

514
00:45:02,554 --> 00:45:04,723
I'm talking about Ri Eung Ryeong.

515
00:45:04,806 --> 00:45:07,059
Thanks to your comrades
getting annihilated,

516
00:45:07,142 --> 00:45:12,439
the director general was cut loose,
and Ri Eung Ryeong swooped in to take it.

517
00:45:20,405 --> 00:45:21,573
"Stay alive."

518
00:45:24,284 --> 00:45:26,328
"You have to survive, no matter what."

519
00:45:27,037 --> 00:45:27,955
Gang Seong!

520
00:45:28,038 --> 00:45:29,373
Stay alive!

521
00:45:29,456 --> 00:45:31,250
You have to survive, okay?

522
00:45:31,333 --> 00:45:33,293
Yeong Gwang!

523
00:45:42,469 --> 00:45:43,345
Those were 66's…

524
00:45:44,680 --> 00:45:47,099
No, those were Yeong Gwang's

525
00:45:48,475 --> 00:45:50,435
last words to me too.

526
00:45:52,354 --> 00:45:53,355
So…

527
00:45:55,983 --> 00:45:56,942
stay alive.

528
00:46:38,191 --> 00:46:42,571
Leave the past behind…

529
00:46:46,241 --> 00:46:48,702
and live as Min-ji's dad.

530
00:47:58,480 --> 00:47:59,940
-Start searching.
-Yes, sir.

531
00:48:05,153 --> 00:48:06,405
We should at least talk to him.

532
00:48:43,900 --> 00:48:44,985
Min-ji.

533
00:48:48,155 --> 00:48:49,614
I'm here, Min-ji.

534
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:54,077
Min-ji?

535
00:49:14,181 --> 00:49:15,348
Min-ji!

536
00:49:15,432 --> 00:49:16,266
Min-ji…

537
00:49:31,740 --> 00:49:32,616
Min-ji.

538
00:49:36,203 --> 00:49:37,078
Min-ji.

539
00:49:59,851 --> 00:50:00,977
I'm sorry, Dad.

540
00:50:02,395 --> 00:50:03,355
I'm scared.

541
00:50:09,653 --> 00:50:10,654
Min-ji…

542
00:50:12,322 --> 00:50:13,490
is alive.

543
00:50:19,621 --> 00:50:21,915
Min-ji…

544
00:50:25,585 --> 00:50:26,670
Min-ji!

545
00:50:35,136 --> 00:50:36,346
Min-ji!

546
00:50:43,854 --> 00:50:44,980
Min-ji!

547
00:50:45,814 --> 00:50:46,857
Kim Min-ji!

548
00:50:52,153 --> 00:50:53,154
Min-ji.

549
00:50:54,865 --> 00:50:55,866
Min-ji!

550
00:51:17,512 --> 00:51:18,513
Min-ji!

551
00:51:22,517 --> 00:51:23,602
Kim Min-ji!

552
00:52:11,733 --> 00:52:13,026
Min-ji!

553
00:52:15,278 --> 00:52:16,321
Kim Min-ji!

554
00:52:23,370 --> 00:52:24,287
Kim Min-ji!

555
00:52:31,753 --> 00:52:32,671
Min-ji.

556
00:52:44,307 --> 00:52:45,266
Min-ji!

557
00:52:46,977 --> 00:52:48,937
It's me! Min-ji!

558
00:52:59,698 --> 00:53:00,865
Min-ji!

559
00:53:10,458 --> 00:53:11,501
Spread out and search.

560
00:53:11,584 --> 00:53:12,502
-Yes, sir.
-Yes, sir.

561
00:53:25,807 --> 00:53:27,142
-Director!
-Director!

562
00:53:28,518 --> 00:53:30,186
-Are you okay, sir?
-Sir.

563
00:53:30,770 --> 00:53:31,604
Get off me!

564
00:53:33,523 --> 00:53:36,693
-What about Kim?
-He's currently at Myeongpo Port.

565
00:53:38,653 --> 00:53:39,779
What about the other two?

566
00:53:40,363 --> 00:53:42,824
Sung Han-soo was already gone.

567
00:53:42,907 --> 00:53:44,159
As for Park Jin-cheol,

568
00:53:44,242 --> 00:53:45,326
he surrendered, but…

569
00:53:45,410 --> 00:53:47,203
He surrendered?

570
00:53:47,954 --> 00:53:49,414
That makes no sense!

571
00:53:49,497 --> 00:53:50,999
The thing is…

572
00:53:51,499 --> 00:53:53,376
It does make sense.

573
00:53:53,460 --> 00:53:55,420
He escaped during transport, you see.

574
00:53:55,503 --> 00:53:57,547
What? Escaped? You little…

575
00:53:59,132 --> 00:54:00,341
What the hell are you guys doing?

576
00:54:00,925 --> 00:54:02,218
You can't do anything right.

577
00:54:05,930 --> 00:54:07,057
Let's get going for now.

578
00:54:07,140 --> 00:54:08,016
-Director.
-Yes, sir.

579
00:54:09,476 --> 00:54:10,310
Here.

580
00:54:15,940 --> 00:54:16,775
Why do you have that?

581
00:54:18,943 --> 00:54:20,862
I found it on the side of the road.

582
00:54:22,864 --> 00:54:24,991
Where's my cash and credit cards?

583
00:54:36,544 --> 00:54:37,378
What's this?

584
00:54:37,462 --> 00:54:38,546
TRANSACTION APPROVED
1,673,000 WON

585
00:54:38,630 --> 00:54:39,798
What? 160,000…

586
00:54:40,590 --> 00:54:42,300
Wait, 1.67 million won?!

587
00:54:45,303 --> 00:54:47,013
Those bastards!

588
00:54:49,057 --> 00:54:51,059
That's actually not bad for them.

589
00:54:55,605 --> 00:54:57,107
Hey, Han-soo.

590
00:54:57,190 --> 00:54:58,316
It's Jin-cheol.

591
00:54:59,317 --> 00:55:01,653
Sorry, it took me a while
to unlock the phone.

592
00:55:01,736 --> 00:55:04,447
Hey, have you heard of
germanium bracelets?

593
00:55:04,531 --> 00:55:05,865
Not sure if they're effective though.

594
00:55:05,949 --> 00:55:08,034
Man, these red snow crabs are huge.

595
00:55:08,118 --> 00:55:10,120
I stocked up on some combat rations.

596
00:55:10,745 --> 00:55:12,330
We need to eat before we fight.

597
00:55:12,413 --> 00:55:14,916
Take that germanium bracelet and stuff it.

598
00:55:14,999 --> 00:55:16,751
How can you eat at a time like this?

599
00:55:17,544 --> 00:55:19,087
-Whose number is this anyway?
-Oh, this?

600
00:55:19,170 --> 00:55:21,339
I took this phone
from one of the SMD agents.

601
00:55:21,422 --> 00:55:23,424
Call me on this number from now on, okay?

602
00:55:24,300 --> 00:55:25,468
Just answer the phone when I do.

603
00:55:25,552 --> 00:55:27,512
Okay, okay!

604
00:55:28,471 --> 00:55:29,389
He nags too much.

605
00:55:30,807 --> 00:55:34,102
DEOKJEON SERVICE AREA

606
00:55:35,019 --> 00:55:38,189
MYEONGPO MOTORCYCLES

607
00:55:38,273 --> 00:55:39,149
Ma'am.

608
00:55:40,859 --> 00:55:44,112
Are you sure you're okay with selling it
for this price?

609
00:55:44,195 --> 00:55:45,780
It's fine.

610
00:55:47,907 --> 00:55:50,535
My husband used to ride this
back in the day.

611
00:55:50,618 --> 00:55:53,246
He's too old for that now.

612
00:55:56,332 --> 00:55:58,543
I'll just buy some good beef with this.

613
00:56:00,461 --> 00:56:01,296
Hold on.

614
00:56:01,921 --> 00:56:04,215
-Yes?
-You're going to ride like that?

615
00:56:14,267 --> 00:56:15,852
-Thank you, ma'am.
-Bye.

616
00:56:34,412 --> 00:56:35,622
Boss!

617
00:56:39,500 --> 00:56:40,835
Boss.

618
00:56:43,213 --> 00:56:45,048
Boss.

619
00:56:47,008 --> 00:56:48,218
Boss!

620
00:56:49,427 --> 00:56:51,429
It's so cold here.

621
00:56:51,512 --> 00:56:53,223
We're screwed, boss.

622
00:56:55,058 --> 00:56:56,142
Boss.

623
00:56:57,101 --> 00:56:58,269
Boss.

624
00:56:58,353 --> 00:56:59,520
Boss!

625
00:57:01,022 --> 00:57:03,024
Hey, the kid.

626
00:57:04,442 --> 00:57:07,028
That little rat.

627
00:57:07,528 --> 00:57:08,738
Hey, go find her.

628
00:57:08,821 --> 00:57:10,615
-Find her.
-Yes, sir.

629
00:57:14,202 --> 00:57:15,286
Our guys…

630
00:57:15,370 --> 00:57:16,204
Grab him.

631
00:57:33,263 --> 00:57:34,889
Open your mouth.

632
00:58:00,540 --> 00:58:02,750
Wait!

633
00:58:02,834 --> 00:58:04,085
Please help me!

634
00:58:04,168 --> 00:58:05,378
Please!

635
00:58:21,102 --> 00:58:23,438
The chairman left you
with his final orders.

636
00:58:24,772 --> 00:58:25,732
You'll take the fall…

637
00:58:28,234 --> 00:58:29,694
for killing that girl.

638
00:58:32,447 --> 00:58:34,824
And then I die too, right?

639
00:58:35,658 --> 00:58:36,701
Where's the body?

640
00:58:37,619 --> 00:58:38,536
Body?

641
00:58:39,746 --> 00:58:40,955
What body?

642
00:58:43,666 --> 00:58:44,500
That one?

643
00:59:06,064 --> 00:59:07,065
Where is it?

644
00:59:13,655 --> 00:59:15,281
You're screwed.

645
00:59:16,074 --> 00:59:18,034
There's no body, dumbass.

646
00:59:20,411 --> 00:59:21,663
That girl

647
00:59:22,413 --> 00:59:24,165
is still alive.

648
00:59:27,377 --> 00:59:29,379
She's still alive. Find her!

649
00:59:29,462 --> 00:59:30,463
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

650
00:59:35,093 --> 00:59:37,136
-Finish up here, then join us.
-Yes, sir.

651
00:59:43,893 --> 00:59:44,894
Hey, lackey.

652
00:59:46,312 --> 00:59:47,522
Do you know

653
00:59:48,356 --> 00:59:50,400
what life tastes like?

654
00:59:51,609 --> 00:59:52,735
Sweet?

655
00:59:52,819 --> 00:59:54,153
Bitter?

656
00:59:55,571 --> 00:59:56,698
Nope.

657
00:59:56,781 --> 01:00:00,535
Guys like you who act tough

658
01:00:00,618 --> 01:00:04,038
may see life as sweet or bitter,

659
01:00:04,706 --> 01:00:05,873
but for thugs…

660
01:00:09,877 --> 01:00:11,212
life tastes like blood.

661
01:00:30,231 --> 01:00:31,274
Over here!

662
01:00:31,357 --> 01:00:32,650
Over here!

663
01:00:33,484 --> 01:00:35,653
Please stop the car!

664
01:00:36,237 --> 01:00:37,196
Please!

665
01:01:26,621 --> 01:01:27,580
Min-ji!

666
01:01:45,723 --> 01:01:48,226
HANGMAN 10-RO

667
01:01:53,189 --> 01:01:54,273
NATIONAL HIGHWAY 87

668
01:02:10,373 --> 01:02:12,458
The rain's coming down hard.

669
01:02:15,002 --> 01:02:17,088
MR. KIM

670
01:02:22,969 --> 01:02:23,803
Hello?

671
01:02:23,886 --> 01:02:25,346
Hangman 10-ro, Poseung-eup.

672
01:02:26,180 --> 01:02:27,348
National Highway 87.

673
01:02:27,974 --> 01:02:29,809
Track the CCTV footage
from ten minutes ago.

674
01:02:29,892 --> 01:02:31,018
What?

675
01:02:31,102 --> 01:02:32,478
It'll show Min-ji's whereabouts.

676
01:02:34,105 --> 01:02:35,231
Mr. Kim.

677
01:02:35,314 --> 01:02:37,775
The only way this ends is by finding her.

678
01:02:38,943 --> 01:02:41,070
So call me once you've tracked her.

679
01:02:43,155 --> 01:02:44,824
Please, Sang-a.

680
01:02:59,213 --> 01:03:01,090
What kind of bullshit is that?

681
01:03:01,173 --> 01:03:02,717
How can we trust that bastard?

682
01:03:03,217 --> 01:03:05,636
Agent Kim is going out of control
to find his daughter.

683
01:03:05,720 --> 01:03:07,388
Once he does,

684
01:03:07,471 --> 01:03:09,557
he'll turn himself in.

685
01:03:09,640 --> 01:03:10,850
What, you think he's crazy?

686
01:03:11,517 --> 01:03:13,769
He knows exactly what will happen
if he turns himself in.

687
01:03:13,853 --> 01:03:17,106
He's a man of his word.

688
01:03:17,189 --> 01:03:18,065
Shut up, you punk!

689
01:03:18,149 --> 01:03:19,233
I'm sorry, sir.

690
01:03:20,359 --> 01:03:21,611
Sir.

691
01:03:21,694 --> 01:03:23,362
I think they have a point.

692
01:03:23,446 --> 01:03:24,363
I agree, sir.

693
01:03:24,447 --> 01:03:27,116
Agent Kim's movements
have been centered around his daughter.

694
01:03:27,700 --> 01:03:29,243
What's the matter with all of you?

695
01:03:29,327 --> 01:03:31,662
Any dad would naturally…

696
01:03:32,538 --> 01:03:34,123
It's only natural, isn't it?

697
01:03:36,334 --> 01:03:39,045
So, his daughter is his weakness.

698
01:03:41,380 --> 01:03:43,549
Look for Kim's daughter right now.

699
01:03:44,175 --> 01:03:45,927
We need to take her hostage first.

700
01:03:46,010 --> 01:03:46,886
Sorry?

701
01:03:47,553 --> 01:03:48,387
Yes, sir.

702
01:03:49,347 --> 01:03:50,598
Take her hostage?

703
01:03:54,352 --> 01:03:57,688
Codename 66
entered Myeongpo Port at 23:01.

704
01:03:58,189 --> 01:04:03,527
CODENAME 66

705
01:04:04,612 --> 01:04:08,282
Subject who appears to be Kim Min-ji
sighted at 23:34.

706
01:04:15,456 --> 01:04:18,417
Subject entered the road in question
at 23:45.

707
01:04:22,254 --> 01:04:23,422
It's that car, right?

708
01:04:24,048 --> 01:04:25,216
You sure she got in?

709
01:04:25,299 --> 01:04:26,550
Yes, she did.

710
01:04:26,634 --> 01:04:28,052
I'll track her location right now.

711
01:04:28,135 --> 01:04:30,805
155D 9884

712
01:04:36,060 --> 01:04:37,603
Thank you for giving me a ride.

713
01:04:38,229 --> 01:04:39,271
Thank you so much.

714
01:04:53,703 --> 01:04:54,704
You haven't found her yet?

715
01:04:54,787 --> 01:04:55,913
We can't find her anywhere.

716
01:04:57,206 --> 01:04:59,333
The lead vehicle just passed by here.

717
01:05:00,626 --> 01:05:01,585
You mean the chairman?

718
01:05:02,878 --> 01:05:04,338
We're en route to the villa.

719
01:05:05,006 --> 01:05:05,923
Understood.

720
01:05:07,299 --> 01:05:09,093
Mr. Nam will join us shortly.

721
01:05:13,264 --> 01:05:14,306
The rain stopped.

722
01:05:17,768 --> 01:05:18,602
Jung.

723
01:05:19,979 --> 01:05:22,273
-Do you know what hojae means?
-Excuse me?

724
01:05:23,232 --> 01:05:24,859
Doesn't it mean a good thing?

725
01:05:25,568 --> 01:05:26,402
That's right.

726
01:05:27,528 --> 01:05:29,613
Any factor that provides a good advantage.

727
01:05:32,783 --> 01:05:34,618
It can also mean "good material."

728
01:05:36,245 --> 01:05:37,079
I'll remember that, sir.

729
01:05:39,623 --> 01:05:40,958
An unexpected advantage…

730
01:05:43,794 --> 01:05:46,005
This is proof that Hye-ri
is blessed with good fortune.

731
01:05:48,466 --> 01:05:50,593
She just delivered herself right to us.

732
01:06:54,949 --> 01:06:58,577
AGENT KIM REACTIVATED

733
01:06:59,161 --> 01:07:01,413
Where did you take my daughter?

734
01:07:01,872 --> 01:07:04,375
I love and cherish Hye-ri so much,

735
01:07:04,458 --> 01:07:06,168
no matter what mistakes she makes.

736
01:07:06,752 --> 01:07:07,962
Let's just go through them.

737
01:07:09,130 --> 01:07:11,340
Effective immediately, we're initiating
an emergency alert protocol.

738
01:07:11,423 --> 01:07:13,467
Is he trying to start a war or what?

739
01:07:13,551 --> 01:07:15,344
They're both after Min-ji right now.

740
01:07:16,053 --> 01:07:17,513
Fire!

741
01:07:17,596 --> 01:07:18,764
You want to have a shootout?

742
01:07:18,848 --> 01:07:22,184
I can make it
so you never see your daughter again.

743
01:07:22,268 --> 01:07:23,644
You can shoot him
and claim it was an accident.

744
01:07:23,727 --> 01:07:25,563
Min-ji, I'm here.

745
01:07:26,605 --> 01:07:27,690
Let's go home now.

746
01:07:28,607 --> 01:07:31,610
Subtitle translation by: Jenny Kim

